//STRINGS FOR ACTIVITY_CHOOSEBASEINFO What\'s In Your Dew Choosing a base for your hair care product is the first and most important step to your hair care regime. No two heads are the same however dewy and hydrated kinks are a must have for natural hair on anyone. The best way to maintain a dewy and hydrated coif is through achieving pH balance. The proper pH balance for one\'s head is within the 4.5-5.5 range(acidic). This acidity is a direct result of the mantle on one\'s hair shaft. The mantel is a thin layer of sebum, salt, and water covering every follicle. It helps to keep the cuticles lining the hair shaft closed which stops the hair from becoming dry which can ultimately lead to breakage. Selecting at least one product from each category below will ensure that your hair\'s pH balance is strengthened and restored.
Water - RoseWater ~ Glycerine - AloeVera ~ TeaTree Oil - Peppermint Oil - Lavender Oil - Almond Oil - Vanilla Extract
//STRINGS FOR ACTIVITY_CHOOSEOILINFO You Look Balm After dewing your hair you must take action to ensure that all of that hydration is sealed in. Sealing one\'s hair is a 2 step process and this is step one. Here you will create a product using all natural waxes and penetrative oils that will seal in hydration and moisturize your hair. There are specific oils that have been proven to penetrate the hair shaft and diminish protein loss. Herbal Shea Butter - White Shea Butter - Murumuru Butter ~ Coconut Oil - Grapeseed Oil - Olive Oil - Babassu Oil
//STRINGS FOR ACTIVITY_CHOOSESCENTINFO Get Glossed This is the final step of your hair care regime and the final step to sealing your hair. There are oils that penetrate your hair and there are oils that simply coat your hair. These coating oils are perfect for sealing in your moisturizer. They diminish water absorption which in turn reduces frizz and preserves the health of your head longer. Using any of the products listed below will achieve the desired results of preservation. We also give you the option of lacing your hair with an aromatic oil mixture for a scent-astic finishing touch! Jojoba Oil - Jamaican Black Castor Oil
